<h1> Basic Algebra </h1>

This is a learning resource page for Algebra, mainly for Part 1 undergraduates. 
<br>
It is not specific to any module or programme. Check your syllabus.


<!-- }}} -->
<!-- {{{ --> <!-- NEWS -->



<!-- }}} -->
<!-- {{{ --> <!-- Lecture notes -->
<h4> Selected Lecture Notes and Other Reading </h4>

The following sets of notes may provide useful support for your studies.
<ul><li>
Some handy notes on 
<!--
<a href="http://www.staff.city.ac.uk/~ra359/courses/X1Algebra/current/AlgebraNotes.pdf">
-->
<a href="AlgebraNotes.pdf">
SETS, COMPLEX NUMBERS,
SEQUENCES AND SERIES, and DIFFERENCE EQUATIONS (provisional version)</a>
(NB, Matrices are not included).
</li><li>
Some handy notes on 
<a href="./X1AlgRels.pdf"> RELATIONS (provisional version) </a> 
</li><li>
Some notes for more advanced students wishing to make 
<a href="http://www.staff.city.ac.uk/~ra359/psfiles/a3.pdf">
Algebra THE NEXT STEP (provisional version)
</a>. 
These notes have been used in the past to help students prepare for 
Part 2 Linear Algebra courses. They are not currently being used for this
purpose, and the `Treasure hunt' refered to in the notes is not happening this
year. 
However, you may find some of these notes useful as 
collateral/support  material for Part 1 Algebra!  
</li>
<li> Some more useful links and references on naive set theory, relations and so on, are <a href="links.html"> here</a>.

</ul>

<!-- }}} -->
